WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:30.163 --> 00:33.644
As I explained on the phone,
our coffins are made in France.

00:33.867 --> 00:37.348
Solid wood, timeless models
and handcrafted finishes.

00:37.704 --> 00:41.026
As for the type of wood,
we have oak, beech and mahogany.

00:41.274 --> 00:44.869
Our selection is available
in 0.7 or 0.85 inch width.

00:45.011 --> 00:48.310
It's important because your father
wanted to be cremated.

00:48.548 --> 00:51.517
The wood you use
doesn't justify your prices.

00:51.951 --> 00:53.566
Your stuff is all recycled.

00:54.788 --> 00:55.550
Ash.

00:56.022 --> 00:57.114
Ash would be nice.

00:57.323 --> 01:00.190
They don't have ash.
Even the oak is Class D.

01:00.393 --> 01:02.156
Look at the knots.

01:02.862 --> 01:05.126
If that's prime cut, I'll be damned.

01:06.332 --> 01:07.993
You're right, it's Class D.

01:10.570 --> 01:11.730
This is disgusting.

01:11.971 --> 01:14.121
Dad would roll over in his grave.

02:50.103 --> 02:56.235
LOVE AT FIRsT FIGHT

03:06.686 --> 03:10.201
Discover 10,000 jobs
offered by the French Army every year!

03:10.857 --> 03:12.791
Come in for a career presentation,

03:13.026 --> 03:15.722
have a personalized interview
and evaluation.

03:16.029 --> 03:19.294
Win T-shirts and blow-up mattresses!

03:19.499 --> 03:22.468
Only a few more days
to meet our career advisors!

03:22.702 --> 03:25.489
Otherwise dial 3240 and say "Army."

03:25.772 --> 03:27.558
When you enlist, we commit.

03:27.807 --> 03:29.900
Dial 3240 and say "Army."

03:56.135 --> 03:57.750
Push harder!

03:58.338 --> 03:59.430
Use your hands!

04:01.207 --> 04:02.538
It took you long enough.

04:02.809 --> 04:05.926
The guy wanted to enlist me.
They must be hard up.

04:06.246 --> 04:08.874
- What did you get?
- A blow-up mattress.

04:14.254 --> 04:15.869
I whipped his ass.

04:16.089 --> 04:17.214
He's 12 years old.

04:17.423 --> 04:19.277
No way, he's at least 14.

04:19.524 --> 04:20.856
Arnaud Labréde!

04:22.195 --> 04:24.129
Oh yeah, we signed you up.

04:24.430 --> 04:25.761
You're kidding me.

04:25.999 --> 04:27.853
Labréde? He's not here?

04:33.873 --> 04:35.124
I'm not fighting a girl.

04:35.275 --> 04:38.267
No one's fighting anyone.
This is self-defense.

04:38.845 --> 04:42.167
Hitting is off-limits
so there's nothing to be afraid oi.

04:42.949 --> 04:44.132
I'm not afraid...

04:44.384 --> 04:45.749
Come on, dude.

04:57.597 --> 04:58.723
Shake hands.

05:17.317 --> 05:19.251
Come on, fight back!

05:20.987 --> 05:22.443
Fight back, it's not over.

05:22.655 --> 05:24.441
What a humiliation, bro!

05:33.800 --> 05:35.085
Bravo, young man.

05:36.803 --> 05:37.633
You okay?

05:38.104 --> 05:39.924
Don't forget your brochure, miss.

05:40.139 --> 05:40.969
You almost ate it.

05:41.474 --> 05:43.237
Did you bite her or what?

05:43.509 --> 05:44.157
No.

05:44.344 --> 05:46.107
I did an armlock.

05:47.080 --> 05:50.595
If that's what girls are like this year,
long live France!

06:05.031 --> 06:05.952
Arnaud?

06:07.700 --> 06:09.133
The door is locked.

06:09.302 --> 06:11.395
I'm taking a bath. What do you want?

06:12.372 --> 06:14.704
It's not easy to talk through a door!

06:15.708 --> 06:17.232
We'll talk later, Morn.

06:28.855 --> 06:30.971
Does the breeze bother you?

06:32.959 --> 06:36.759
I thought you were spending
summer vacation with Xavier and Victor.

06:38.331 --> 06:40.993
But Manu says
you're staying here to work.

06:42.335 --> 06:44.189
Were you planning on telling me?

06:44.704 --> 06:45.659
Of course I was.

06:46.372 --> 06:50.024
I thought I'd help out
and start learning the trade.

06:50.676 --> 06:53.463
In the current context,
it's a serious commitment.

06:54.013 --> 06:54.866
Do you understand?

06:55.415 --> 06:57.394
You think I'm not committed enough?

06:57.984 --> 07:01.067
What I mean is that you're free
to look elsewhere.

07:01.354 --> 07:03.288
Contact other companies or whatever.

07:03.656 --> 07:05.635
The important thing is to plan ahead.

07:06.426 --> 07:09.020
I don't want to plan ahead,
I want to work here.

07:09.328 --> 07:10.420
You see?

07:10.596 --> 07:12.359
He shouldn't leave now anyhow.

07:13.199 --> 07:14.325
Our new catalogue.

07:15.268 --> 07:16.963
We might not be a big company,

07:17.570 --> 07:20.653
but with some good PH
orders will pour in this summer.

07:21.507 --> 07:22.462
Right, Arnaud?

07:24.177 --> 07:25.155
Cool.

07:29.115 --> 07:31.299
Our garden shelters are all unique.

07:31.551 --> 07:34.031
For your home, I would suggest

07:34.253 --> 07:36.733
either the Rochelais or the Panama.

07:37.390 --> 07:39.358
The photos give you a rough idea.

07:39.525 --> 07:41.823
We adapt the structure
to your home,

07:42.061 --> 07:43.722
your desires and your needs.

07:43.963 --> 07:46.329
The important thing is overall harmony.

07:47.433 --> 07:50.061
Madeleine?
Could you come here a second?

07:51.537 --> 07:53.801
Sweetheart,
which one do you like best?

07:59.378 --> 08:02.734
You don't have to buy one.
They're used to rejection.

08:03.149 --> 08:04.912
- Madeleine!
- It's true.

08:05.117 --> 08:08.143
If you want to buy something useless,
don't ask me.

08:09.121 --> 08:12.386
Our products are factory-made
and guaranteed for 5 years.

08:12.592 --> 08:14.924
Cut the salesman crap.

08:15.127 --> 08:18.278
You'd never say: "Our sheds are shit
AND they fall apart!"

08:18.464 --> 08:20.796
Even if they were of gold,
they're dumb.

08:21.067 --> 08:22.853
Are you a landscaping expert?

08:23.102 --> 08:26.219
Tell us which one you like best,
not your life story!

08:26.439 --> 08:27.451
Drop it, Arnaud.

08:33.111 --> 08:34.477
What about that one?

08:34.679 --> 08:36.375
That's the one I like best.

08:39.118 --> 08:40.698
We'll let you think it over.

08:43.456 --> 08:45.606
Maybe it wasn't against you.

08:45.825 --> 08:48.089
Maybe she doesn't like wood.

08:48.294 --> 08:53.095
She did it on purpose.
She made me look like a total moron.

08:54.867 --> 08:58.496
Who gives a shit?
You sold your hut, end of story.

09:00.640 --> 09:01.823
Your thing is beeping.

09:02.108 --> 09:03.120
Shit.

09:10.516 --> 09:12.097
It's fucking infested here.

09:12.818 --> 09:14.968
Catfish eat up all the diversity.

09:15.187 --> 09:17.371
Soon there'll be nothing else left.

09:21.327 --> 09:23.181
Son-of-a-bitch catfish.

09:59.398 --> 10:00.831
Want some help?

10:05.371 --> 10:06.736
You want some help?

10:07.540 --> 10:09.064
I didn't bust it.

10:11.077 --> 10:13.045
Of course you didn't bust it.

10:15.381 --> 10:16.905
It's like if I did this.

10:21.621 --> 10:23.600
You have to visualize your target

10:24.223 --> 10:26.589
as if it were 12 inches behind itself.

10:27.693 --> 10:28.705
You get it?

10:29.528 --> 10:30.381
No.

10:32.798 --> 10:35.494
You have to strike beyond your target.

10:38.270 --> 10:39.794
Beyond your target.

10:55.054 --> 10:56.180
You get it now?

11:10.903 --> 11:11.995
I can't be here

11:12.238 --> 11:14.263
and out there hustling for clients.

11:15.274 --> 11:16.400
Put it down here.

11:19.612 --> 11:20.772
It's gross.

11:24.016 --> 11:28.373
So I thought that...
I'd let you do it yourself.

11:28.621 --> 11:30.202
I'm going to work alone?

11:30.623 --> 11:32.602
It'll be a good experience.

11:33.359 --> 11:36.658
If word gets around,
we'll be overrun with orders.

11:37.763 --> 11:39.549
It's no big deal, you know.

11:40.166 --> 11:42.316
It's like Lego building blocks.

11:48.441 --> 11:50.409
We'll probably need to hire on.

11:50.609 --> 11:52.304
The sky's the limit.

11:53.012 --> 11:55.162
What's she doing with my roof tiles?

12:12.398 --> 12:13.979
She's really nuts.

12:14.366 --> 12:15.856
Yeah, she's kind of weird.

12:16.068 --> 12:18.366
Totally off the hook is more like it-.

12:23.342 --> 12:24.775
Good luck, bro.

13:00.246 --> 13:02.942
Do you have a vegetable garden?
For the earthworms.

13:04.350 --> 13:05.681
Are you spying on me?

13:06.418 --> 13:07.703
You swim weird.

13:07.920 --> 13:10.013
It's not weird, it's the combat swim.

13:10.256 --> 13:11.951
- What?
- Combat swim. Drop it.

13:16.896 --> 13:19.319
I'm sorry I bit you the other day.

13:19.532 --> 13:23.161
If there's anything I can do to make up,
just let me know.

14:28.868 --> 14:29.880
Goddammit!

14:50.289 --> 14:52.109
Are you trying to drown it?

14:54.226 --> 14:55.477
Make yourself at home.

15:09.708 --> 15:11.164
What do you want me to do?

15:11.543 --> 15:14.330
You can adopt it.
Ferrets are easy to tame.

15:14.847 --> 15:15.802
That's a ferret?

15:16.015 --> 15:17.027
A baby ferret.

15:18.083 --> 15:19.937
He'll love you like a morn.

15:20.185 --> 15:22.881
Like a morn?
Animals don't have emotions.

15:23.088 --> 15:26.205
If you die,
your cat will eat your face after 3 days.

15:27.493 --> 15:28.824
We'll turn him loose.

15:29.028 --> 15:30.393
He's too little.

15:30.596 --> 15:33.747
He stinks of chlorine,
his mother would reject him.

15:34.099 --> 15:36.215
He'd die instantly in nature.

15:39.004 --> 15:41.757
I can't keep it.
I'm joining the army in september.

15:42.341 --> 15:43.524
Permanently?

15:46.245 --> 15:47.496
Then I'll keep it.

15:49.882 --> 15:51.543
We're so crashing the party.

15:51.750 --> 15:54.617
No, it's not.
No one told us not to come.

15:55.955 --> 15:58.890
Excuse me,
you know a babe named Violet?

16:00.359 --> 16:01.519
No?

16:02.027 --> 16:03.278
Thanks anyhow.

16:07.132 --> 16:09.157
Saskatoon, in saskatchewan.

16:09.435 --> 16:10.288
What cartoon?

16:10.569 --> 16:11.854
Saskatoon.

16:12.705 --> 16:14.684
I thought you were going to Canada.

16:14.907 --> 16:16.238
That is Canada.

16:16.709 --> 16:18.643
Why the hell are you going there?

16:18.911 --> 16:20.401
It's better than here.

16:20.913 --> 16:22.938
I'm rotting away here.
France is dead.

16:23.248 --> 16:25.876
Get real. There's no future here.

16:26.819 --> 16:28.673
So you're not coming back?

16:28.921 --> 16:31.788
Depends what happens.
At least I'll learn English.

16:31.957 --> 16:36.610
You don't have to go that far.
There must be shitholes in England too.

16:37.463 --> 16:38.441
He's right.

16:38.664 --> 16:40.154
The idea isn't to stay close.

16:40.399 --> 16:42.879
- What is the idea?
- Yeah, what is the idea?

16:46.238 --> 16:47.671
I'll be right back.

16:51.076 --> 16:53.226
Victor doesn't give a shit about us.

16:54.146 --> 16:57.946
We take an interest in his stuff
and he just walks off-.

16:59.585 --> 17:01.200
The two of us by the BBQ... ...

17:01.420 --> 17:04.901
This is a preview of what it'll be like
when he splits.

17:05.491 --> 17:06.287
Oh yeah?

17:06.525 --> 17:08.459
It'll be just the two of us-.

17:09.428 --> 17:11.089
But we'll stick together.

17:12.798 --> 17:14.083
Did you know...

17:14.366 --> 17:17.665
that your cat will eat your face
after 3 days?

17:25.844 --> 17:27.128
Here we go.

17:32.317 --> 17:34.831
This will fall apart in ten years' time.

17:37.456 --> 17:39.390
This is what we need.

17:41.794 --> 17:42.954
You don't give a shit?

17:43.462 --> 17:44.895
Can we get this?

17:47.166 --> 17:48.292
What for?

17:49.134 --> 17:50.954
To make a cage for the ferret.

17:54.206 --> 17:57.858
- Your name, please?
- Labréde. L-A-B-R-E-D-E.

18:00.179 --> 18:03.501
I have a Mr. Eric Labrede registered
for the same company.

18:05.217 --> 18:07.071
That's not us. It was our father.

18:07.486 --> 18:10.967
You want me to transfer
his loyalty points to your account?

18:11.190 --> 18:12.316
What should I do?

18:13.559 --> 18:14.719
What do you say?

18:20.432 --> 18:21.353
What do I do?

18:22.000 --> 18:23.524
How should I know? Arnaud?

18:23.735 --> 18:26.761
I don't know. Take them.
They'll be lost otherwise.

18:27.039 --> 18:29.337
Okay.
It'll pay for your netting.

18:29.875 --> 18:32.332
- We'll take them.
- Okay.

18:58.270 --> 18:58.952
Hey.

19:01.306 --> 19:02.136
How's it going?

19:02.808 --> 19:03.786
Things coming along?

19:06.078 --> 19:07.329
Yeah.

19:07.946 --> 19:09.914
I've almost finished the frame.

19:10.716 --> 19:15.005
You know, pillars like these can support
a very large amount of weight-.

19:15.621 --> 19:16.781
Great.

19:22.728 --> 19:24.582
You know where the soldiers are?

19:24.997 --> 19:27.022
The truck over at the lake is gone.

19:27.266 --> 19:28.597
I know, they left.

19:29.001 --> 19:30.969
They've moved on to the next town.

19:33.939 --> 19:35.099
Never mind.

19:41.780 --> 19:43.236
You want me to take you?

19:47.920 --> 19:49.251
I'll get a helmet.

20:59.224 --> 21:00.202
Fuck!

21:02.728 --> 21:04.013
Don't get all mad.

21:12.671 --> 21:13.797
I want to sign up.

21:14.273 --> 21:16.298
We're closed. Come back tomorrow.

21:16.541 --> 21:18.520
For starters,
take your helmets off.

21:22.080 --> 21:23.092
Arnaud!

21:25.117 --> 21:26.209
I didn't recognize you.

21:28.186 --> 21:28.868
Well?

21:31.089 --> 21:32.340
Has it sunk in yet?

21:34.192 --> 21:36.171
Let's say that, now I can see...

21:36.595 --> 21:38.745
better beyond stuff.

21:44.636 --> 21:46.615
Can't you help her? It's important.

22:20.272 --> 22:21.432
This is fucked.

22:41.993 --> 22:44.621
Army Preparation Camp
1st Parachute Dragoon Regiment

22:48.433 --> 22:50.890
Are you enlisting
or going to summer camp?

22:51.870 --> 22:56.125
For the regiment I want to join,
you have to take a preparation course.

23:00.345 --> 23:03.132
You have to take a course
to join the army?

23:05.117 --> 23:07.051
I thought you just showed up.

23:08.286 --> 23:12.416
It depends on the regiment.
The one I want is super hard.

23:14.159 --> 23:15.649
Super hard, like what?

23:17.396 --> 23:19.876
Super hard,
like you sweat your guts out.

23:20.132 --> 23:23.101
If you want to sleep, you dig a hole.

23:23.301 --> 23:24.552
There's physical combat.

23:24.736 --> 23:27.159
You have to swim
with 60 lbs. On your back.

23:27.339 --> 23:28.590
You ever swim with Rangers?

23:29.875 --> 23:30.455
No.

23:31.710 --> 23:35.009
There's an entrance exam.
You have to eat a raw sardine.

23:35.213 --> 23:38.364
First the head,
then the eyes, entrails and scales.

23:38.717 --> 23:40.241
That's what you want to do?

23:40.552 --> 23:42.531
They have the best survival techniques.

23:42.888 --> 23:44.469
After that, I'll be prepared.

23:45.657 --> 23:46.942
Prepared for what?

23:48.393 --> 23:49.644
To survive.

23:51.763 --> 23:53.742
I got that. But survive what?

24:07.179 --> 24:08.942
How do you know the recruiter?

24:09.681 --> 24:11.615
Maybe I'm interested too.

24:13.919 --> 24:14.874
Oh yeah?

24:15.086 --> 24:18.055
We talked one day.
He showed me some technical stuff.

24:18.390 --> 24:19.482
Like what?

24:20.025 --> 24:20.878
Stuff.

24:22.427 --> 24:24.088
Stop playing Mr. Mystery Man.

24:27.766 --> 24:30.394
You ever heard
oi "double visualization"?

24:38.276 --> 24:40.369
You're going to hit my shoulder.

24:40.645 --> 24:44.399
You need to double visualize
my shoulder 12 inches behind itself.

24:44.950 --> 24:47.976
In other words,
as it there were another me behind me.

24:48.253 --> 24:50.232
You visualize him but you hit...

24:52.824 --> 24:54.917
I think I double visualized you well.

24:55.727 --> 24:57.388
You dislocated my shoulder.

24:58.430 --> 24:59.442
Your turn.

25:00.265 --> 25:01.550
I don't hit girls.

25:02.133 --> 25:04.431
Oh yeah, I forgot. You bite them.

25:44.943 --> 25:46.558
I think it's raining less.

25:48.280 --> 25:49.372
Son of.

26:30.755 --> 26:33.269
Can you explain this shit?
Where were you?

26:33.858 --> 26:35.473
Answer me! Where were you?

26:37.062 --> 26:40.714
You fucked up!
For once I give you some responsibility!

26:40.932 --> 26:44.231
Importation of 23% in volume
and the French only 8%,

26:44.436 --> 26:47.189
a trend that solidifies the colossal
German trade surplus,

26:47.405 --> 26:49.703
which means they sell more
than they buy abroad,

26:49.908 --> 26:52.570
which is the opposite tor the French.
Since 2005, as a matter of fact...

27:40.925 --> 27:43.951
I'm Madeleine Beaulieu.
Your sons are working at my place.

27:44.596 --> 27:46.029
Oh, yes. Good evening.

27:46.931 --> 27:50.196
I brought you a present
to make up for the storm and all.

27:50.669 --> 27:52.432
That's very sweet. Thank you.

27:52.971 --> 27:54.097
Should I take it?

27:56.574 --> 27:58.394
It's baby chicks for the ferret.

27:59.511 --> 28:01.877
- Baby chicks?
- Don't worry, they're dead.

28:02.147 --> 28:04.297
They're frozen. It's more practical.

28:04.516 --> 28:06.814
I got them at a chicken breeding farm.

28:07.185 --> 28:10.302
They sell their losses
to dry dogfood companies.

28:11.156 --> 28:14.455
Powdered baby milk isn't good
for ferrets. They eat meat.

28:14.626 --> 28:17.618
They need solids,
otherwise you change their nature.

28:19.964 --> 28:21.454
That's what dogfood does.

28:23.868 --> 28:26.382
I don't know what to say. Thank you.

28:27.005 --> 28:28.131
It's sweet of you.

28:28.473 --> 28:29.758
Will you stay for dinner?

28:30.642 --> 28:32.667
No, I just came
to give you the present.

28:32.877 --> 28:35.141
I insist. It would make me very happy.

28:36.715 --> 28:38.376
I'll put this in the fridge.

28:38.650 --> 28:39.833
The freezer.

28:43.955 --> 28:45.047
Hey.

29:01.539 --> 29:03.359
Can you imagine a fire in here?

29:07.812 --> 29:11.077
Your mom invited me for dinner.
You don't mind?

29:12.851 --> 29:13.772
No.

29:15.086 --> 29:16.747
You put him in here? Not bad.

29:27.031 --> 29:28.646
You make coffins too?

29:30.068 --> 29:31.854
No, that was for my dad.

29:32.237 --> 29:34.694
They were all ugly
so we said we'd make our own.

29:35.874 --> 29:38.206
But you need a special license.

29:39.110 --> 29:41.897
We didn't have enough time.

29:42.413 --> 29:44.779
Now we don't know what to do with it.

29:47.085 --> 29:48.666
It's not bothering anyone.

29:49.921 --> 29:51.013
No.

29:55.627 --> 29:57.083
Are you in college?

29:57.462 --> 29:59.316
I have a Master's
in economic modeling.

30:00.265 --> 30:01.755
And what's that for?

30:02.400 --> 30:04.857
The idea is to anticipate future events

30:05.069 --> 30:06.923
in order to adapt to them now.

30:07.472 --> 30:10.293
But since future events won't exist,
it's pointless.

30:10.708 --> 30:12.289
I dropped out this year.

30:12.477 --> 30:13.842
I can understand.

30:14.078 --> 30:16.444
Years of college
with no job guarantee...

30:16.881 --> 30:18.496
The recession, unemployment...

30:18.716 --> 30:19.876
It's not easy.

30:20.451 --> 30:22.874
There's far worse in store
than unemployment.

30:23.087 --> 30:26.511
But since we only focus on trivia,
we don't see it coming.

30:26.991 --> 30:28.777
What don't we see coming?

30:29.494 --> 30:30.859
The end.

30:31.095 --> 30:32.676
The end of what?

30:33.898 --> 30:35.354
"The end." Our extinction.

30:36.301 --> 30:37.097
Oh, I see.

30:37.836 --> 30:39.417
What should we look out for?

30:39.971 --> 30:41.586
Take your pick.

30:41.773 --> 30:43.263
Hunger strikes, religious wars,

30:43.808 --> 30:45.469
drought, global warming,

30:45.677 --> 30:48.612
inversion of the poles,
nuclear plants blowing up...

