The idea is to...

58:03.213 --> 58:04.999
break up the shape of the face.

58:08.585 --> 58:10.348
You apply it with two fingers...

58:12.756 --> 58:14.576
in diagonal streaks.

58:21.398 --> 58:22.683
You want to conceal...

58:26.269 --> 58:27.520
the patterns of your nose...

58:31.975 --> 58:33.340
your mouth...

58:41.985 --> 58:43.418
and your eyes.

58:50.494 --> 58:52.314
That way, everything disappears.

59:02.506 --> 59:05.259
- It burns.
- That's normal. Don't touch.

59:06.476 --> 59:07.636
Look.

59:14.017 --> 59:15.177
Very good.

59:18.188 --> 59:19.348
Now it's my turn.

59:30.367 --> 59:31.493
What's that?

59:33.503 --> 59:34.595
Nothing.

59:35.505 --> 59:38.474
They made me unit leader
for the orienteering race.

59:44.314 --> 59:45.235
Close your eyes.

01:00:11.842 --> 01:00:12.854
Everyone smile!

01:00:16.279 --> 01:00:18.543
The first unit to attain the objective

01:00:19.116 --> 01:00:22.051
will have the honor of raising
the regiment's flag on saturday.

01:00:23.520 --> 01:00:24.441
Is that clear?

01:00:24.754 --> 01:00:26.119
Yes, sir.

01:00:30.527 --> 01:00:31.812
Good luck, Labréde.

01:00:33.430 --> 01:00:34.442
Get the upper hand.

01:00:49.880 --> 01:00:51.404
Leduc, are we good?

01:00:51.781 --> 01:00:52.964
Yeah, it's over there.

01:00:53.250 --> 01:00:54.911
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

01:01:07.564 --> 01:01:10.192
Charlie, Romeo speaking.
State your coordinates.

01:01:10.600 --> 01:01:11.965
Lieutenant schliefer?

01:01:12.602 --> 01:01:14.934
I can't hear you, Lieutenant.

01:01:15.572 --> 01:01:18.393
There is no Lieutenant schlieter!
This is Romeo. Over.

01:01:19.342 --> 01:01:20.434
Madeleine, stop it.

01:01:20.977 --> 01:01:23.639
Charlie, Romeo speaking.
State your coordinates.

01:01:23.847 --> 01:01:25.098
Where are we, Jordan?

01:01:25.682 --> 01:01:28.276
We're either here... or here.

01:01:29.319 --> 01:01:31.014
But I'd say we're heading...

01:01:32.756 --> 01:01:33.438
that way.

01:01:33.924 --> 01:01:36.518
That's east. The target is due south.

01:01:36.660 --> 01:01:40.289
Jordan's having a hard time.
I think we're totally lost.

01:01:40.497 --> 01:01:41.327
Sum up, Samara.

01:01:41.531 --> 01:01:42.691
"Lost" is not a coordinate.

01:01:42.933 --> 01:01:45.117
The target isn't really south.

01:01:46.336 --> 01:01:47.951
Yes, it is. Look, Jordan.

01:01:48.205 --> 01:01:50.139
The hill slopes downwards.

01:01:50.507 --> 01:01:51.963
That changes the direction.

01:01:52.542 --> 01:01:53.725
Are you sure?

01:01:55.178 --> 01:01:56.429
Give it here.

01:01:57.047 --> 01:01:59.231
- Give the map back!
- One minute.

01:02:01.184 --> 01:02:03.004
No, give it back right now!

01:02:03.286 --> 01:02:04.571
Let me deal with it.

01:02:04.955 --> 01:02:06.047
Listen to me.

01:02:32.382 --> 01:02:33.360
What?

01:02:34.684 --> 01:02:36.834
Doesn't he have the compass?

01:02:54.704 --> 01:02:56.467
I'm sorry! Okay?

01:03:39.282 --> 01:03:41.102
You have the compass by the way!

01:04:28.665 --> 01:04:29.848
Where are you going?

01:04:30.166 --> 01:04:31.827
I have a life to go back to.

01:04:52.822 --> 01:04:53.948
Good evening.

01:04:54.457 --> 01:04:55.788
Would you like anything?

01:04:56.226 --> 01:04:57.352
A beer, please.

01:04:57.560 --> 01:04:59.494
We only have alcohol-free.

01:05:01.231 --> 01:05:03.745
Maybe with the regional specialties?

01:05:05.735 --> 01:05:07.714
An alcohol-free beer is fine.

01:05:11.741 --> 01:05:13.072
Everything alright?

01:05:13.543 --> 01:05:14.635
It's nothing.

01:05:15.879 --> 01:05:17.335
Vigipirate security plan.

01:05:18.982 --> 01:05:20.643
Would you like anything?

01:05:21.518 --> 01:05:22.678
No.

01:05:43.706 --> 01:05:45.685
You insinuating I don't have a life?

01:05:45.875 --> 01:05:48.810
I'm not insinuating, I'm saying it:
You have no life.

01:05:49.412 --> 01:05:52.006
You don't like people.
You eat things that disgust you.

01:05:52.215 --> 01:05:55.150
When you do sports,
you look like you want to die.

01:05:56.920 --> 01:05:59.514
You fight to stay in the army
but you hate it.

01:05:59.722 --> 01:06:02.543
I'm sorry, life is the opposite
of everything you do.

01:06:02.792 --> 01:06:05.124
And building dumb wood huts is life?

01:06:05.361 --> 01:06:07.625
It might be dumb but I like doing it.

01:06:07.797 --> 01:06:09.913
- You don't like anything.
- It's not true.

01:06:10.200 --> 01:06:11.326
- It's not true?
- No.

01:06:11.568 --> 01:06:13.092
Tell me one thing you like.

01:06:13.303 --> 01:06:15.066
I like lots of things.

01:06:15.438 --> 01:06:16.530
For example...

01:06:26.115 --> 01:06:27.571
For example, I like dogs.

01:06:27.784 --> 01:06:28.967
Dogs?

01:06:31.788 --> 01:06:33.153
Like that one?

01:06:36.493 --> 01:06:37.653
Exactly.

01:06:40.497 --> 01:06:41.930
Hey, doggie.

01:06:45.068 --> 01:06:46.592
Don't waste your breath.

01:06:47.670 --> 01:06:49.524
Hey, puppy 1109!

01:06:58.181 --> 01:06:59.136
Come here, puppy.

01:08:05.982 --> 01:08:07.597
You got some extra room?

01:08:37.880 --> 01:08:40.872
If you want to go back
with your loser friends, it's time.

01:08:58.701 --> 01:09:00.066
Come on, let's go.

01:09:05.441 --> 01:09:06.624
What now?

01:09:06.876 --> 01:09:10.073
We'll survive. We'll adapt.
That's what you wanted, right?

01:09:10.380 --> 01:09:11.870
What do you have on you?

01:09:13.282 --> 01:09:15.045
I have a knife. That's all.

01:09:16.219 --> 01:09:19.643
I have a flashlight, mess kits
and the camouflage tarpaulin.

01:09:19.988 --> 01:09:22.321
We're totally underequipped. Great.

01:09:22.558 --> 01:09:24.674
Wait, I have one combat ration left.

01:09:25.094 --> 01:09:26.220
Lamb stew.

01:09:26.429 --> 01:09:28.613
Toss it. We don't need their stuff.

01:09:31.100 --> 01:09:32.112
Lamb stew...

01:09:32.468 --> 01:09:35.255
They'll be no help
when everything goes up in flames.

01:10:10.440 --> 01:10:12.055
This is a perfect spot.

01:10:13.309 --> 01:10:14.833
There's everything we need.

01:10:15.044 --> 01:10:16.170
It's great.

01:10:25.688 --> 01:10:27.121
What are you doing?

01:10:27.323 --> 01:10:28.483
What're you doing?

01:10:28.725 --> 01:10:30.386
I'm going to build a shelter.

01:10:31.994 --> 01:10:33.325
What's so funny?

01:10:33.796 --> 01:10:34.922
Nothing.

01:10:35.398 --> 01:10:36.524
It's cool.

01:11:02.191 --> 01:11:03.715
It's not finished yet.

01:11:04.393 --> 01:11:06.361
I'll put some storage space here.

01:11:07.196 --> 01:11:09.221
There's a bookshelf in the back.

01:11:10.266 --> 01:11:11.187
Great.

01:11:11.400 --> 01:11:12.378
Not bad, huh?

01:11:17.607 --> 01:11:20.064
I'll get some moss to insulate the roof.

01:11:22.211 --> 01:11:24.145
Don't go that way. I laid traps.

01:11:29.218 --> 01:11:30.708
Not that way either.

01:11:32.221 --> 01:11:32.835
No?

01:11:33.890 --> 01:11:36.256
You should probably go around.

01:11:37.927 --> 01:11:39.258
This way?

01:11:58.581 --> 01:11:59.946
What next?

01:12:04.587 --> 01:12:06.407
Nothing. We just enjoy.

01:12:08.224 --> 01:12:10.556
Can't we enjoy and do something?

01:12:11.627 --> 01:12:13.652
We shouldn't expend calories.

01:12:24.440 --> 01:12:26.624
Why don't you make a fishing line?

01:12:41.290 --> 01:12:42.905
Do I have to wait long?

01:12:43.659 --> 01:12:45.274
You have to wait.

01:14:10.179 --> 01:14:11.134
What's the goal?

01:14:12.848 --> 01:14:15.476
The goal is to bury them gently

01:14:15.718 --> 01:14:17.083
without breaking them.

01:14:21.557 --> 01:14:22.922
What's the point?

01:14:23.859 --> 01:14:25.474
Nothing.

01:14:27.563 --> 01:14:28.996
You want to try?

01:14:42.311 --> 01:14:44.461
What do you think about
while you do it?

01:14:45.581 --> 01:14:46.593
Nothing.

01:15:04.333 --> 01:15:05.584
I can't do it.

01:15:07.570 --> 01:15:09.185
Then you won't survive.

01:15:12.274 --> 01:15:15.573
It you cant concentrate
on a pine needle, you can't survive.

01:15:20.182 --> 01:15:21.968
Knowing how to pass the time...

01:15:22.985 --> 01:15:27.274
not doing or thinking about anything
in particular... that's surviving.

01:15:28.024 --> 01:15:29.480
Otherwise you go crazy.

01:16:04.794 --> 01:16:06.284
What's going on?

01:16:09.365 --> 01:16:10.980
I'm passing the time.

01:19:12.548 --> 01:19:15.244
Hang on,
I'll wrap the wire around once more.

01:19:15.517 --> 01:19:16.973
You think it'll hold?

01:19:17.319 --> 01:19:18.684
Of course it will.

01:19:19.054 --> 01:19:20.749
It's a real pro's trap.

01:19:25.728 --> 01:19:27.093
Turn it the other way.

01:19:44.246 --> 01:19:45.907
Wow, looks like France.

01:19:50.619 --> 01:19:51.779
I'm hungry.

01:19:52.421 --> 01:19:53.706
You're always hungry.

01:19:54.390 --> 01:19:55.755
Did you hear something?

01:19:56.458 --> 01:19:57.789
No, it was my stomach.

01:20:01.096 --> 01:20:03.690
The wildlife here
is starting to piss me off-.

01:20:08.037 --> 01:20:10.335
We still have those weird hazelnuts.

01:20:13.475 --> 01:20:15.261
They have zero protein.

01:20:24.420 --> 01:20:27.014
We should've taken more snickers
from the army.

01:21:00.923 --> 01:21:03.221
Come on, eat! Don't be fussy.

01:21:04.593 --> 01:21:05.958
It's disgusting.

01:21:09.531 --> 01:21:11.055
Shit, look at this.

01:21:13.369 --> 01:21:15.189
I'm sure you can eat the bones.

01:21:15.804 --> 01:21:17.772
I bet it's full of good stuff.

01:21:24.446 --> 01:21:25.777
I can't eat this.

01:21:26.215 --> 01:21:27.830
Don't waste food!

01:21:28.050 --> 01:21:30.166
I swear to God, this is horrible.

01:21:31.353 --> 01:21:32.365
I'm done.

01:21:32.621 --> 01:21:34.555
I'll stick to fishy hazelnuts.

01:21:35.290 --> 01:21:37.474
You don't know what you're missing.

01:21:42.831 --> 01:21:44.651
I think I'm lying on a rock.

01:21:46.802 --> 01:21:49.066
Are we sleeping directly on the ground?

01:21:49.872 --> 01:21:51.203
No, not at all.

01:21:51.807 --> 01:21:54.230
I made a one-inch mattress of lichen.

01:21:56.512 --> 01:21:57.945
It's okay.

01:21:58.147 --> 01:21:59.330
It's fine.

01:21:59.548 --> 01:22:01.243
Want me to remove the rock?

01:22:01.517 --> 01:22:02.802
No, don't worry.

01:22:04.186 --> 01:22:05.801
I'll curl up around it.

01:22:13.262 --> 01:22:14.445
By the way...

01:22:14.997 --> 01:22:16.658
why are you whispering?

01:22:18.167 --> 01:22:20.590
I don't want to scare off the game-.

01:22:21.170 --> 01:22:22.455
Oh, I see.

01:22:52.734 --> 01:22:53.860
Are you okay?

01:22:54.036 --> 01:22:55.196
Don't look.

01:23:01.877 --> 01:23:03.458
I'll stay over here, okay?

01:23:39.014 --> 01:23:40.993
You're shaking. I'll get a jacket.

01:23:53.529 --> 01:23:54.689
Madeleine!

01:23:56.198 --> 01:23:57.324
Are you okay?

01:26:34.122 --> 01:26:36.215
Open your eyes. Keep your eyes open!

01:26:36.425 --> 01:26:37.403
Look at me!

01:26:37.993 --> 01:26:39.085
Look at me!

01:29:26.127 --> 01:29:29.927
She's upstairs.
She hasn't woken up yet, but she's fine.

01:29:36.271 --> 01:29:37.363
Thanks.

01:29:38.306 --> 01:29:40.422
They can't get the fire under control.

01:29:41.109 --> 01:29:43.225
900 hectares have already burnt.

01:29:43.945 --> 01:29:46.459
The town they found you in
burned down.

01:29:46.681 --> 01:29:48.137
Wiped off the map-.

01:29:50.619 --> 01:29:52.052
We were lucky.

01:29:56.458 --> 01:29:58.312
How much is 900 hectares?

01:29:58.660 --> 01:29:59.752
200,000 trees?

01:29:59.995 --> 01:30:02.259
More like 2 million. You hall asleep?

01:30:03.131 --> 01:30:06.396
It's a big deal.
It'll affect the price of wood.

01:30:07.669 --> 01:30:10.149
We're okay,
I stocked up before. You'll see.

01:30:11.406 --> 01:30:12.839
If you want to, that is.

01:30:13.541 --> 01:30:15.304
I'm not forcing you.

01:30:19.414 --> 01:30:23.612
Can you imagine the waste?
All because some idiot tossed a cigarette.

01:30:24.185 --> 01:30:26.881
People don't realize
how fragile forests are.

01:30:29.324 --> 01:30:31.918
Sometimes forest fires occur naturally.

01:30:32.694 --> 01:30:34.958
The forest just bursts into flames.

01:30:35.530 --> 01:30:38.124
- Where did you hear that?
- On TV.

01:30:39.434 --> 01:30:44.269
When the forest reaches
its maximum development...

01:30:44.439 --> 01:30:47.374
when there's really no more room,
a fire breaks out.

01:30:47.575 --> 01:30:48.701
Everything burns.

01:30:49.277 --> 01:30:52.474
Afterwards, the forest starts afresh.

01:30:53.949 --> 01:30:55.314
Everything starts over.

01:31:01.523 --> 01:31:04.117
But most of the time...

01:31:04.592 --> 01:31:07.914
it's some idiot who tosses a cigarette.

01:31:09.965 --> 01:31:11.489
The other case is rare.

01:31:18.206 --> 01:31:19.992
How's the tomato soup?

01:31:22.310 --> 01:31:23.402
Wonderful.

01:32:19.300 --> 01:32:21.268
You don't hurt anywhere?

01:32:21.669 --> 01:32:22.522
Not at all.

01:32:23.772 --> 01:32:25.797
Barely 3 on a scale of one to ten.

01:32:26.641 --> 01:32:28.427
Did you have to rate your pain?

01:32:28.843 --> 01:32:30.174
What did you say?

01:32:30.378 --> 01:32:32.528
Four for the head. I had a headache.

01:32:36.718 --> 01:32:37.696
Here?

01:32:43.124 --> 01:32:44.136
It's funny...

01:32:44.859 --> 01:32:47.157
I'd never have thought of rating pain.

01:32:47.695 --> 01:32:48.855
Higher UP-

01:32:51.066 --> 01:32:53.523
Three's not bad.
It leaves room for improvement.

01:32:55.170 --> 01:32:56.831
We can call it a day.

01:32:57.839 --> 01:32:59.454
We'll recover slowly.

01:32:59.674 --> 01:33:01.255
I'm already feeling better.

01:33:01.476 --> 01:33:02.397
Oh yeah?

01:33:02.544 --> 01:33:04.660
Of course, I was better trained.

01:33:05.480 --> 01:33:08.176
Nice to hear,
next time you'll carry me.

01:33:10.251 --> 01:33:11.502
Next time...

01:33:12.420 --> 01:33:14.035
it's going to be different.

01:33:16.424 --> 01:33:18.881
Next time,
we need to be better prepared.

01:33:19.861 --> 01:33:20.714
We will be.

01:33:21.529 --> 01:33:22.712
We'll be ready.

01:33:23.198 --> 01:33:24.176
That's right.

01:33:24.933 --> 01:33:28.130
We won't be caught by surprise.
We won't improvise.

01:33:29.237 --> 01:33:30.670
We'll be on the look-out.

01:33:33.708 --> 01:33:34.891
On the look-out.

01:33:36.945 --> 01:33:38.310
On our guard.

